This paper is about kernel matrix approximation, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The paper proposes algorithms that run in linear time and provide provable guarantees for various downstream learning tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the most relevant sub-category. Other possible sub-categories include cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these fields also deal with similar problems and techniques.
